What is a Commit ?
A commit in Git is a saved snapshot of your project at a specific point in time.
It is  like pressing "Save Game" in a video game. If something goes wrong later, you can return to that saved point.

What is branching?
Branching in Git is the process of creating a separate line of development to work on new features or fixes without affecting the main codebase.

What is Merge conflict ?
A merge conflict occurs when Git cannot automatically combine changes from two branches because the same part of a file was modified differently in both branches.

